squeakr
------------------------------------------
Squeakr is a k-mer-counting and multiset-representation system using the
recently-introduced counting quotient filter (CQF) Pandey et al. (2017), a
feature-rich approximate membership query (AMQ) data structure.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libboost_system1.66-1.66.0-1
  libboost_thread1.66-1.66.0-1
  libbz2_1-1.0.8-2
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  zlib0-1.3.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libboost-devel-1.66.0-1
  libbz2-devel-1.0.8-2
  make-4.4.1-2
  zlib-devel-1.3.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/splatlab/squeakr

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/splatlab/squeakr/archive/refs/tags/v0.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack squeakr-0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./squeakr-0.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/squeakr-0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/squeakr-0.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(squeakr)
  /usr/bin/squeakr.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/squeakr.README
  /usr/share/doc/squeakr/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/squeakr/README.md
  /usr/share/squeakr/test.fastq

